introduction: Dear participant,  This survey is the second of a two-stage experiment, which aims to test how consumers use digital wallets and to study their comfort level with using cryptocurrency. To participate, you must have completed the first stage - 'Data Marketplace 1'.    The survey should take approximately 10 minutes to complete.    We will ask you to:  1. Provide the addresses of the auctions you created.  2. Give feedback on your experience using the data 2101 marketplace.    This stage will determine the bonus you will receive.    Important: This survey is completely anonymous and will not record any of your personal information. In no way we will ask or receive access to your personal details or digital assets. You may choose to exit the experiment whenever you wish.

feedback: The metamask addon consumes an excessive amount of resources. Under normal conditions, this would stop me from experimenting with the market because I do not understand what reason a browser addon would have to consume such a high amount of CPU and RAM usage. The marketplace itself was quite simple to use. But I still fail to understand what the purpose is. I could see this as being useful if I were selling private information on a blackmarket, but I fail to see what interest a buyer would have in knowing random details of an unknown person.
